## <a id="1-4-38"></a>v1.4.38

**Release Date:** October 29, 2018

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* The bundled ClamAV open source distribution is now v0.100.2.

### Security Fixes

This release includes the following security fixes:

* [CVE-2018-15378](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-15378):
  A vulnerability in ClamAV's MEW unpacking feature in v0.100.1 and earlier
  could allow a denial-of-service (DoS) condition.

* [CVE-2018-14680](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-14680):
  An issue in mspack/chmd.c in libmspack before 0.7alpha prevented it rejecting blank CHM filenames.

* [CVE-2018-14681](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-14681):
  Bad KWAJ file header extensions could cause a one- or two-byte overwrite.

* [CVE-2018-14682](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-14682):
  An off-by-one error in the TOLOWER() macro for CHM decompression.
  Additionally, v0.100.2 reverted v0.100.1's patch for [CVE-2018-14679](https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2018-14679)
  and applied this newer fix instead.

For the ClamAV v0.100.2 release notes, see the [ClamAV blog](https://blog.clamav.net/2018/10/clamav-01002-has-been-released.html).

